<span class="displaytext">the (candidate full) presidential committee today announced its leadership in four michigan congressional districts. <p>the campaign has named chairs for the 10th, 12th, 13th, and 15th congressional districts, which include the detroit area and surrounding counties. </p><p>"we are excited to join together in support of mayor (candidate last), who has the most public executive leadership experience of anyone running and has displayed the kind of strong leadership our country needs," said kim porter-hoppe, who will serve as chair of the campaign's efforts in the 15th congressional district. </p><p>additionally, the campaign named chairs for several counties within those four districts, including huron, lapeer, macomb, monroe, oakland, sanilac and st. clair shores counties. </p><p>"we're excited that mayor (candidate last)'s campaign in michigan continues to grow," said rep. candice miller, (candidate last)'s michigan state chair. "these leaders in their respective communities will help communicate mayor (candidate last)'s message to michigan voters â€“ and we're confident that voters will see rudy is the right man to be our nominee and our next president." </p><p><strong><u>about rudy's michigan congressional district chairs:</u></strong> </p><p><strong>terri kowal, 10th district chair</strong> <br/> kowal is clerk of shelby township and has been a (PARTY NAME) state committee member and a delegate to the (PARTY NAME) national convention. </p><p><strong>victoria rewiako-smiley, 12th district co-chair <br/> </strong>vici rewiako-smiley, of warren, is a homemaker who has served in numerous roles with the macomb county (PARTY NAME) party. </p><p><strong>william susick, 12th district co-chair <br/> </strong>bill susick, of (candidate last) township, is retired from a career in the auto industry. he is also a veteran of the u.s. navy. </p><p><strong>john r. axe, 13th district chair <br/> </strong>axe, of grosse pointe farms, is an attorney and president of the law firm axe &amp; ecklund. he also headed the group citizens for michigan, which sought to make changes to the state's constitution. </p><p><strong>kim m. porter-hoppe, 15th district chair <br/> </strong>porter-hoppe, of ypsilanti, is chair of the alliance of black (PARTY NAME)s and the elections coordinator for salem township. she is coordinator for the washtenaw county family support network and was appointed to the president's committee for people with mental retardation, whose name she helped change to the president's committee on people with intellectual disabilities. </p><p><u><strong>about rudy's michigan county chairs:</strong></u> </p><p><strong>jeff bohm, st. clair county chair</strong> <br/> bohm, of china, is a real estate developer who serves as a commissioner in st. clair county, as well as chair of the public safety judiciary committee. </p><p><strong>mark gaertner, huron county chair</strong> <br/> gaertner is the huron county prosecutor and lives in austin. </p><p><strong>donald a. hunt, sanilac county chair</strong> <br/> hunt, of croswell, serves on the board of commissioners in sanilac county. </p><p><strong>gene lawter, lapeer county co-chair</strong> <br/> lawter, of columbiaville, is a retired general motors executive who serves on the elected executive board of the lapeer county (PARTY NAME) party. </p><p><strong>katherine lawter, lapeer county co-chair</strong> <br/> lawter serves on the elected executive board of the lapeer county (PARTY NAME) party and is a resident of columbiaville. </p><p><strong>william axtell, oakland county chair</strong> <br/> bill axtell, of ferndale, is a founding member and past president of ferndale area (PARTY NAME)s and a former president of the ferndale chamber of commerce. he was appointed by governor john engler to the michigan commission on disability concerns, and was named to the metro detroit advisory board of the mackinac center for public policy earlier this year. axtell also serves on the oakland county (PARTY NAME) party executive committee. </p><p><strong>rep. jack brandenburg, macomb county chair</strong> <br/> rep. brandenburg, of harrison township, represents house district 24 in the michigan state legislature, which includes st. clair shores, harrison and lake townships. </p><p><strong>angelique rea, wayne county chair <br/> </strong>rea, of lincoln park, is the vice-chair of the 13th district (PARTY NAME) committee. she has served as a dearborn victory center associate for president george w. bush's 2004 campaign, as lincoln park city chair and taylor victory center assistant to the director for the devos for governor campaign, and is co-founder of the wayne county young conservatives club. </p><p><strong>david lamontaine, monroe county chair <br/> </strong>lamontaine, of newport, is president of the monroe county deputy sheriff's association. </p><p><strong>rhonda runco, wayne county chair</strong> <br/> runco, of dearborn, has been a candidate for michigan state senate in the 6th district. </p><p><strong>peter simmons, washtenaw county chair</strong> <br/> simmons, of saline, serves on the executive committee of the washtenaw county (PARTY NAME) committee.</p></span>



